UP ALL NIGHT  debuted on the NATIONAL ARIA CHARTS in Jan 2003 at  number 3, and the AIR INDEPENDENT CHARTS at  number 1.					 
At the 17TH ANNUAL ARIA AWARDS held in Sydney, Australia in October 2003, UP ALL NIGHT won BEST ROOTS/BLUES ALBUM & BEST INDEPENDENT ALBUM.  It also won the ARTISAN AWARDS for BEST PRODUCED ALBUM & BEST ENGINEERED ALBUM (with CHRIS WILSON)
				
This album reached GOLD record sales 4 weeks after release, PLATINUM sales in October 03 and DOUBLE PLATINUM  in February 04. After 91 weeks (15/11/04) this album was STILL at No.7 - and was voted No.50 in the Triple J HOTTEST 100 Jan 2004.
